#+
# Name:
#    _REDUCE_DARK_HELLO_
#
# Purpose:
#    Sets up data-reduction tasks and data for the REDUCE_DARK recipe.
#
# Language:
#    Perl5
#
# Description:
#    The script performs the following tasks.
#    -  Sets the USE_VARIANCE steering header.
#    -  Create error array using the read noise only.
#    -  Performs the standard per-frame preparation tasks.  See
#    _PREPARE_SINGLE_FRAME_ for more details.
#
# Steering Headers:
#    USE_VARIANCE = LOGICAL
#       Whether or not variance processing is to occur.  This equates to
#       argument USEVAR.
#
# Arguments:
#    USEVAR = LOGICAL (Given)
#       Whether or not to create and propagate variance arrays.  [1]
#
# Notes:
#    -  This primitive is suitable for UFTI, IRCAM, and Michelle 
#    in imaging mode.
#
# Authors:
#    MJC: Malcolm J. Currie (JAC)
#
# Copyright:
#    Copyright (C) 1998-2003 Particle Physics and Astronomy Research
#    Council.  All Rights Reserved.
#
#-

# Set the steering headers
# ========================

# Processing is so simple, there's no need for a _REDUCE_DARK_STEER_
# primitive.  Just need to set the USE_VARIANCE steering header.
    my $usevar = $_REDUCE_DARK_HELLO_{USEVAR};
    $usevar = defined( $usevar ) ? $usevar: 1;
    $Frm->uhdr( "USE_VARIANCE", $usevar );

# Prepare the single frame.
# =========================

# Adds variance arrays, subtracts the bias, differences chopped beams,
# and adds world co-ordinate system.
     _PREPARE_SINGLE_FRAME_

# Podule
# ======

=head1 NAME

_REDUCE_DARK_HELLO_ -- Sets up data-reduction tasks and data for REDUCE_DARK recipes.

=head1 DESCRIPTION

The script performs the following tasks.

=over 4

=item *

Sets the USE_VARIANCE steering header.

=item *

Create error array using the read noise only.

=back

=head1 STEERING HEADERS

=over 4

=item USE_VARIANCE = LOGICAL

Whether or not variance processing is to occur.  This equates to
argument USEVAR.

=back

=head1 ARGUMENTS

=over 4

=item USEVAR = LOGICAL (Given)

Whether or not to create and propagate variance arrays.  [1]

=back

=head1 NOTES

=over 4

=item *

This primitive is suitable for INGRID.

=item *

Performs the standard per-frame preparation tasks.  See
L<_PREPARE_SINGLE_FRAME_|_PREPARE_SINGLE_FRAME_> for more details.

=back

=head1 AUTHORS

MJC: Malcolm J. Currie (JAC)

=head1 COPYRIGHT

Copyright (C) 1998-2003 Particle Physics and Astronomy Research
Council.  All Rights Reserved.

=cut
